commit 6db4636162a2b1633a7822634c484eb4ed51881a
Author: Atvantiq <Atvantiq@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 22 16:58:12 2026 +0530

    Address codex review: Wyoming law fix, hubs-only, static-server 404
    
    [P1] Wyoming final paycheck was "within 5 business days" for both
    termination and resignation — incorrect. W.S. 27-4-104(a) requires the
    next regular payday in both cases (verified against Wyoming DWS guidance).
    This was live, indexable, incorrect YMYL data.
    
    [P1] Publish only the three curated state hubs; delete the minimum-wage,
    final-paycheck and pto-payout child routes. Those rendered mostly template
    variants (60-77% cross-state vocabulary overlap) without the hub's sourced
    local analysis, so they read as thin/scaled content. A child route may
    return only with its own separately sourced, route-specific content.
    Sitemap 203 -> 194; only the 3 state hubs remain jurisdiction pages.
    
    [P2] serve_static_export.py now sends a real HTTP 404 for missing paths
    (previously served 404.html with a 200 status, a soft-404), matching the
    production static host so the "gated routes 404" e2e assertions hold here too.
    
    Maintenance guard: the sitemap and CA/AU directory grids auto-link a record
    once it passes the gate, but those routes are deleted. Added explicit
    restore-the-route comments; the contentQuality test already fails loudly if
    a CA/AU record becomes indexable without its route.
    
    Verified: 242 unit tests, tsc, production build (exactly 3 hub pages emitted,
    no child routes), 0 broken internal links across 195 pages, static server
    returns 404 for missing paths, seo-remediation e2e 14/14 under the static
    config, and no 320px overflow / clipped-interactive on the modified hub.

